The paper deals with interference alignment in wireless cellular systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of linear precoding and message-passing backhaul network architecture suggests a focus on signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper proposes a topologically robust scheme, which involves designing algorithms and protocols that can handle uncertain or changing network topologies, making computer science theory (cs.DS) another likely sub-category.
